Package: ubuntu-game-handheld
Source: ubuntu-game-session
Version: 0.6
Architecture: all
Maintainer: Ken VanDine <ken.vandine@canonical.com>
Installed-Size: 18
Depends: ubuntu-game-session, hhd, acpi-call-dkms
Section: misc
Priority: optional
Description: Ubuntu Game Session autologin for handheld gaming PCs
 Configures GDM to automatically log in to Ubuntu Game Session on every boot,
 suitable for handheld gaming PCs (Lenovo Legion Go, Steam Deck, and similar).
 .
 Installs and configures:
  - GDM autologin into Ubuntu Game Session on every boot
  - Handheld Daemon (HHD) for TDP and controller management
  - HHD overlay for in-game quick access
  - Seamless switching between Ubuntu Game Session and Ubuntu desktop
  - Virtual keyboard for touchscreen / handheld input
 .
 Depends on ubuntu-game-session and hhd. Remove the package to fully revert
 to original Ubuntu behaviour.
